{"title": "When condo owners fight over the right to build extra roofs", "tags": "business", "timestamp": "2023-10-15", "content": "An increasing number of owners of private apartments have been hitting the roof when some neighbours in their condominiums build unwanted structures right under their noses.\nOne of the most common disputes concerns awnings erected by owners of ground-floor units, who want to shield their small gardens or yards from litter falling from above."}